sql:
SELECT DISTINCT variable_type
FROM variables
ORDER BY variable_type;

external_knowledge:
- "fresh buds" metaphorically refers to children;
- "dawn of the 1990s" refers to the year 1990;
- The order of birth is represented by the ascending order of date_of_birth.

sql:
SELECT child_id, variable_id, value 
FROM child_variables
WHERE value > (SELECT AVG(value) FROM child_variables);

SELECT AVG(birth_weight) AS average_birth_weight
FROM children
WHERE date_of_birth < '2000-01-01';

SELECT child_id, outcome_date
FROM health_outcomes
ORDER BY outcome_date DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "young sprouts" is a metaphor for children;
- "flourished" and "grown stronger" imply significant weight gain which is considered healthy;
- "nourishment of time" refers to the duration over which weight gain has occurred, typically since birth;
- "wandered from their birthweight" symbolizes the difference between the initial and final weight measurements, indicating growth;
- Healthy weight gain is defined as an increase of at least 1 unit in the dataset.

